on, and did major work on the mechanisms of surround suppression, on the logic of corticothalamic feedback, and more. Together with other colleagues at my Institute, I helped write a brief description of his work: &lt;a href="https://www.ucl.ac.uk/ioo/news/2024/jan/eulogy-professor-adam-sillito" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" translate="no"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://www.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;ucl.ac.uk/ioo/news/2024/jan/eu&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;logy-professor-adam-sillito&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; .</description><guid isPermaLink="false">111738336543940414</guid><pubDate>Thu, 11 Jan 2024 16:48:27 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Dimos Karamanlis</title><link>https://qoto.org/@dimokaramanlis/111731598581509792</link><description>&lt;span class="h-card"&gt;&lt;a class="u-url mention" href="https://neuromatch.social/@jonny" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;@&lt;span&gt;jonny&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="h-card"&gt;&lt;a class="u-url mention" href="https://neuromatch.social/@alicia_izquierdo" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;@&lt;span&gt;alicia_izquierdo&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="h-card"&gt;&lt;a class="u-url mention" href="https://neuromatch.social/@manisha" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;@&lt;span&gt;manisha&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; In the retina, people have started to match cell types across species using transcriptomics. Also, cell types are typically well defined because of the tiling principle (dendritic fields of same-type cells typically "repel" each other).Recent awesome work here: &lt;a href="https://www.nature.com/articles/s41586-023-06638-9" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://www.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;nature.com/articles/s41586-023&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;-06638-9&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">111738600268908147</guid><pubDate>Thu, 11 Jan 2024 17:55:29 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>martenson</title><link>https://mastodon.world/@martenson/111730227354882646</link><description>"OpenAI says it‚Äôs ‚Äúimpossible‚Äù to create useful AI models without copyrighted material"10 years ago three dudes from Sweden were hunted by FBI, Interpol and their own government for challenging copyright laws and seeking a fresh approach without ever profiting from it. üè¥‚Äç‚ò†Ô∏èNow venture capitalist-backed corporations will sell us our own copyrighted material at a premium. Working tirelessly to embed it in every product designed from now on so you will not be able to avoid it. üí∞</description><guid isPermaLink="false">111739108292020094</guid><pubDate>Thu, 11 Jan 2024 20:04:43 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Boris Barbour</title><link>https://mastodon.social/@BorisBarbour/111739820495687669</link><description>&lt;a href="https://www.theguardian.com/law/2024/jan/11/south-africa-accuses-israel-of-genocide-gaza-the-hague-international-court-of-justice" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" translate="no"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://www.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;theguardian.com/law/2024/jan/1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;1/south-africa-accuses-israel-of-genocide-gaza-the-hague-international-court-of-justice&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">111739820495687669</guid><pubDate>Thu, 11 Jan 2024 23:05:50 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Spencer LaVere Smith</title><link>https://neuromatch.social/@sls/111739870102335131</link><description>cool postbac job at the Allen using LLMs to parse experimental parameters  &lt;a href="http://labrigger.com/blog/2024/01/11/i-plant-seeds/" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" translate="no"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;http://&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;labrigger.co